   Preparing The Subversion Directory
   ──────────────────────────────────
      1. Open a terminal window
      2. Change to the docker image directory

            i.e.
            cd /data/dataworkspace/svn-docker

      3. Create a new directory to be the mount point for the subversion working directory

            mkdir svn-working-dir

      4. Mount the local subversion working directory to the new mount point (as root user)

            mount -o bind /data/dataworkspace/<subversion-working-directory>/ svn-working-dir/


   Building Images
   ───────────────

      docker build -t <tag> <source-dir>

      docker build -t svn-test-platform .


   Running An Image (Creating A Container)
   ───────────────────────────────────────
      docker run -it --rm --privileged \
         -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY \
         -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix \
         --hostname svn-test \
         --name svn_test_instance \
         svn-test-platform


   Attaching To A Running Image (Creating A New Terminal)
   ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      docker exec -it <container-id> bash

      docker exec -it svn_test_instance bash
